Taco Lindo is a hidden gem in Amsterdam! This cozy spot offers an authentic Mexican dining experience with a menu that's small but packed with flavor. Each taco feels like a trip to a different part of Mexico, featuring fresh ingredients and delicious homemade sauces that make every bite special. The Beef Birria and Cochinita Pibil are personal favorites--tender, perfectly seasoned, and incredibly satisfying. The option to add fresh onions, coriander, and lime for free gives it that extra touch of authenticity.

The atmosphere is relaxed and welcoming, with a small seating area that feels intimate yet vibrant. You can tell that quality is a priority here, as they focus on dine-in rather than delivery, ensuring that each dish is served fresh and hot. The staff are warm and knowledgeable, happy to answer questions or recommend a dish if you're unsure what to try.

If you're looking for real Mexican food in Amsterdam, Taco Lindo is the place to go! Great food, great vibe, and truly dedicated service. [{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzekxHU1V3EAE","rating":5,"name":"Monica M.","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113944174080037868402?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I came to this place on my visit to Amsterdam in mid-October 2024.

The first time I visited was in a slight panic trying to find takeaway places to order a quick late night meal that catered for my allergens.  By that point, I'd walked around for about 30 minutes trying to find a place with no luck, until I came to Hearth on 11 Oct 2024.  They'd sadly JUST stopped food service when I arrived, but the lovely owner, Marcus, took pity on my plight and offered some excellent gluten free and vegan quinoa sushi with dressing for free.  I was amazed by his wonderful generosity that I made a point to come and visit to try the menu out properly when my friend from London arrived.

And that we did.  We visited on Sunday 13 October as walk-ins and everything from the food (presentation and flavour) the non-alcoholic cocktails, the ambience, and the service was nothing short of amazing.  Unfortunately Marcus wasn't there the night I visited as a sit-down guest, but I did offer him one promise...this review, so I send my heartfelt gratitude for his kindness and generosity.  He has a wonderful business.  The food was amazing...I couldn't fault the flavours and textures.  Please do yourself a favour and go - you will not be disappointed by the inventiveness of the dishes and drinks at this place.

Thank you again! Hubby and I went here last night, and honestly everything was outstanding. The service was super friendly, and jokey as well. The music was so interesting and not too loud as I had read in other reviews, and we were quite near some big speakers. The whole ambience and decor of the restaurant is well thought out.

Now the food? It was delicious. We ordered quite a few dishes and loved every single one! Plus the presentation? Like a Michelin star restaurant without the scary prices. We had the Leek and Potato soup, bread and olive starter, Mexican sushi, buckwheat gnocchi, and mushroom red lentil scallop. All dishes were amazing and definitely plentiful.

You can tell everything has been well thought out with this restaurant. There aren't enough stars to give this restaurant, I was truly blown away by the quality of the food. Both the presentation, texture and taste was just magnificent. You get a high dining experience only combined in plates that are actually filling! The ambience was great the music very nice but not disturbing. The waiter was an absolute sweetheart excited about the food helping with recommendations, serving the food in a really nice way. name: Sins of Sal
description:
The sinful sister of restaurant and mezcaleria Salmuera - Sins of Sal is a late-night bar & restaurant of contemporary cocktails, Latin guilty pleasures, and natural wines in the center of Jordaan. As the name suggests, Sins of Sal celebrates sin, fun, and decadence in creative cocktails and Latin food.
From Miami Vice Negronis to freezer martinis with mezcal-brined olives, Sins' cocktail menu is inspired by the favorite guilty pleasures of the bar team - with a focus on minimum waste and big flavor. The food menu is a collage of Mexican and Latin-inspired street food with decadent twists in small dishes. And the wines? All natural and non-Latin of course.

The cocktails are works of art, which get the same passionate description as art from the mixologists. Highly unique combinations, refreshing new ideas and perfectly balanced. We tried them all and every new addition and  our favourite is without a doubt the Paloma but all of the others are pretty much on the same top pedestal. The food is the most accurate representation of the concept, indulgence. We once ordered one dish 5 times on one night because it was just that addicting (the Tuna taco's) and the ever evolving menu leaves you wanting more and more. Kom langs en ervaar zelf waarom Food Brothers Amsterdam de plek is om te genieten van lekker eten, halal-verantwoordelijk en geweldige service!

name: Salsa Shop
description: Discover the vibrant flavors of Mexico at Salsa Shop Haarlemmerstraat, a top-notch Mexicaans fast casual restaurant in Amsterdam. Savour authentic Mexican cuisine right in the heart of the city. Eager for a hearty lunch in Amsterdam? Our restaurant caters to all your cravings. From smoky, grilled meats to fresh, zesty salsa, our menu is a feast for all. Whether you're looking for a restaurant near you, or wanting to dive into delicious Mexicaans food, Salsa Shop Haarlemmerstraat is the place to be. Why wait?

Absolutely recommend trying the food here. They do a great job with the flavours, the meat, even their Mexican coffee!

I expected a expensive dining experience but somehow we were gooooood with a beer each while sharing 9 tacos between us 3. Which made it a very reasonably priced dinner! Desserts are good, the skull candy was such a fun surprise, but could skip if you have done justice to the main dishes :)

Overall, it's worth the hype! I came here at night and my first look from outside is that it reminds me of the gta 5 motorcycle club.
The place seem to be always full, a bit loud (good kind of loud), everyone is talking and having fun.
The food was very good, the portions are on the smaller side and a bit costly but still worth the price in my opinion.
The people who work here are generally very nice, but they aren't for the average guy (I am not used to these kind of places), it felt like there was some sort of etiquette when ordering and interacting with them that I sadly don't know about and I could see the disappointmentin the waiter's eyes every time I needed to order something knew or ask him something but this is my own fault I guess.
If you come here as a couple you will be spending at least 50-70 euros.
When you reserve your place online you will need to pay 10 euros per person, however, it will be deducted from the bill, which is very good.
Overall, I think the people who are used to these kind of places will LOVE it and and those who aren't might find it normal or above average.","published_at":"3 weeks ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-22T18:41:41","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPF4m0Cz5SHCVA5arRL9VEtngYDKsu4qO8gHueA=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMB6fTZtar_XVfDttrWk11ulBjCzwXxOzrkzP3v=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMmqh-THY-fWpxKgOpiywoWkWQLT3vRkvMxVAAd=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMQRrtIwCJgw-JVq-BJUINSooN3PdJFevX6MkTh=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPKMmp6PAAqTc1c1zOgkkRSLyR--UygZicrwDBa=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP-TBEs0-N_edee6F9gLZETyD_IOfi5QXnS5bdr=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPqnWpTDmELmmJjRAiz1aBNt4P9LnleEpioHxTI=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM-sbSdFuXjp98GBB8qKYWoF2kAXRX4Jm0KpoRO=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNhbjf8NHIg9MdCCjCpSOzQdY9CBQLaRbjWrvew=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOtGTxI1k1WEz8pr-JSCokDLr9e1FhuXRg3ISOn=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM-uyG9SrGrFXP9JanyTlwoEBYCc7Mm0WcSceK6=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNWR8gfEIt3JsJYnWa46i4Ysmz8pItsqn6QUs30=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOSzr1aixU2SIag7dxsrRmbnrYxVO64nCjEJzJ2=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNIemY2Rll3EAE","rating":5,"name":"Lisa Praster","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110800463857041224277?hl=en-GB","review_text":"This place... it's my absolute favorite restaurant in whole of Amsterdam, and that says something! The decor is simple but charming, and the service is friendly and welcoming.

What truly stole the show were the tacos. I tried the vegetarian taco special: beer tempura-battered mushroom paired with a mix of fresh, flavorful ingredients. Absolutely delicious! Topped with the two sauces provided at the table, every bite was perfection. I could've easily ordered a second plate.

To end the meal, I had the tres leches dessert. While I've had slightly better versions elsewhere, this one was still delightful and perfectly enjoyable.

name: Cuddle Pub
description: Looking for an escape from the busy shopping street of Nieuwendijk or a spot to duck away from Dam Square? Look no farther than The Cuddle Pub, which is conveniently located on Nieuwe Nieuwstraat, a quiet location away from the crowds. Cuddle Pub has the Best Grill in Amsterdam, Using New Method of Grilling by Steam and Fire which results a Juicy Soft Steak, Burger and Chicken. As well as Best Tacos in Town with Excellent home made Mexican Spicy, ingredients and Spectacular Mexican taste. We welcome locals, Tourists, Families and Groups as well for Events and Parties. It's been years since my first time here, Bakers & Roasters is one of Amsterdam institutions for brunch/lunch. I ordered the veg brekkie (price: 18 euro).
The space is pretty narrow, and the tables are very close to each other. Most of the times there is some waiting time, but the service is very fast, and you are in and out within the hour. Tap water is served immediately (nice touch! Many Amsterdam places will  try to sell you overpriced bottled water).

The food is nice, in my case, simple and well cooked (poached eggs were perfectly cooked). I liked the spicy jelly in combination with the dish.
If I need to find a flaw: probably the size of the coffee cup, quite small for my preferences, I love a large cup of coffee vs. the 120ml size of their flat white.
The staff is friendly and is attentive.","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-10-14T14:29:17","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipN8_J5TEIVPupBKYM6XY9ZpN-UlYP0xWnsn76MM=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMx234wbUy1PGYnzqkVOAdZWUuMKj1QOMGIYRuO=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM5ufIHR12uDS-jffNk-I0m7M0Xjswtayuk0U0V=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURIM2VpdWtnRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Vahid Shahani","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100656582473981744870?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Baker & Roasters is such a gem! So in spite of the storm outside we had a fantastic dinner. We hope something similar will be organized soon and under better weather circumstances so more people can enjoy it!

In addition to the food the drinks and service are also great. We enjoyed the smokey paloma the most. Staff was attentive and (unneccessarily) apologized when one course took slightly longer.

The restaurant also looks really nice. The decor is warm and neat. Bar seats looked great as well. I couldnt figure out if these seats can be booked specifically (like at the sister restaurant) but we d definitely go for them if that was an option.

All in all highly recommend a visit. name: Aubergini Restaurant
description: Aubergini is a unique homemade concept inspired by Mexican, Italian, and Japanese kitchens. As an inclusive cuisine we offer organic meat, chicken and fish as well as glutenfree and vegan options. We use daily fresh and organic (where possible) ingredients to make Burgers, Bowls, Wraps, Sandwiches en drinks. We make pretty much everything ourselves from Low fat Beef Burgers to pure Mineral Water. Connect with us via our website. Looking forward to welcoming you.

Nestled near our Airbnb, Bunk is a restaurant that not only delivers on quality but surpasses it in every imaginable way.

The menu at Bunk is a testament to creativity and finesse. Every dish we tried was a masterpiece, both in taste and presentation. The freshness and flavor of the ingredients were evident in every bite, each component thoughtfully selected and expertly combined. It's clear that Bunk takes immense pride in sourcing the best ingredients, transforming them into artful creations that delight the senses.

On our first night, we were so impressed that we decided to return the following evening to explore more of the menu. Amazingly, each dish we tried the second night was just as spectacular as the first, if not more so. The consistency in quality and the continuous surprise of new flavors left us in awe. It's rare to find a restaurant that excels across the board, but Bunk manages to do just that.

The drinks were another highlight of our experience. Each cocktail was crafted with the same attention to detail as the food, perfectly complementing the dishes and enhancing the overall dining experience.

In our opinion, Bunk is hands down the best restaurant in Amsterdam. It's a hidden treasure that deserves to be celebrated. If you find yourself in this beautiful city, do yourself a favor and visit Bunk. name: New Dutch Amsterdam
description:
Mooi aan de prinsengracht gelegen restaurant voor ontbijt, lunch en diner, waar heerlijke 'fusion'-gerechten geserveerd worden in een warme- en gezellige omgeving.

Reserveren slechts mogelijk op donderdag, vrijdag en zaterdagen vanaf 16:00 uur tot 20:00 uur. Geen reserveringen
Restaurant New Dutch breakfast, lunch and dinner beautifully located on the canal side amidst the hustle and bustle of the city. Authentic culinary traditions from around the world with a Dutch twist in a warm, cozy, hospitable and vibrant setting.
Reservations for dinner only on thu, fri and sat. from 4PM.

name: soupenzo - spiegel
description: Our promise is that we serve you fresh and honest food that is organic and healthy. We do this in the tradition of homemade soup, salad and bakery items. With our well-equipped kitchen we are professional, but certainly not industrial. This means that everything we do is handmade and prepared from start to finish. That gives us the opportunity to prepare food with love and care. You can see and taste that work has been done on it. We think that is super important.

name: iBoenda
description:
Ontdek de authentieke smaak van Indonesie bij iBoenda. Met liefde bereid door een Indonesische moeder, bieden wij verse, huisgemaakte maaltijden vol rijke, traditionele smaken. Laat je verrassen door onze uitgebreide cateringopties en afhaalmaaltijden die de echte Indonesische keuken naar je tafel brengen. Proef de passie, proef de liefde!
Discover the authentic taste of Indonesia at iBoenda. Lovingly prepared by an Indonesian mother, we offer fresh, homemade meals full of rich, traditional flavors. Be surprised by our extensive catering options and takeaway dishes that bring the true Indonesian cuisine to your table. Taste the passion, taste the love!

First up, I tried the Gado-Gado, a delightful mix of veggies with peanut sauce. The dish included cabbage, green beans, and eggs, all topped with a rich and thick peanut sauce that provided a wonderful peanut flavor. The vegetables were perfectly boiled, adding a satisfying texture to the dish.

I've eaten in Indonesia too...I'm not exaggerating. They also do take aways and an equivalent to 'Just Eat'. I ate in the restaurant twice it was that good. I am only in Amsterdam for a few days but I guarantee, I will be visiting iBoenda a second and hopefully a third time again before I leave. I hope my mum won't ever get to read this as she doesn't use the internet, but as much as I love her Indonesian cooking, this Indonesian restaurant is far better and that is saying something, because I love my mum's cooking. If you miss Indonesian food, or whether you have never tried it, I absolutely recommend you eat in and get a take away too as you will not be disappointed with the food and price. name: Salmuera
description:
Casa del Asado y Mezcal. From Argentina to Mexico, Salmuera brings together Argentinian asado and empanadas, Peruvian ceviches, and Latin American street food at the same family table. Sal's mezcaleria started as the first one in the Netherlands in 2015, developing into one of the most extensive collections in Europe of over 150 different bottles. Salmuera's cocktails are influenced by the South American kitchens & ingredients, pairing perfectly with every dish on the menu.

Salmuera is part of a small Latin hospitality family, La Familia Amsterdam. Don't forget to visit Chamuyero Carniceria & Deli & Sins of Sal in the neighborhood!

name: Restaurant Cancun Amsterdam
description:
At Cancun Amsterdam, we blend the vibrant spirit of Latin culture with the rich flavors of Mexican and Caribbean cuisine to create a unique dining and entertainment experience.
From tantalizing dishes prepared with fresh, authentic ingredients to dynamic events featuring the best in salsa, bachata, and Latin music, we're dedicated to bringing the essence of Cancun to Amsterdam.
Join us for a journey of taste, rhythm, and unforgettable moments.

Where Flavors and Rhythms Meet.

name: Rosario Cocina Mexicana
description:
Bij Rosario werken we met een kleine, regelmatig wisselende kaart, met gerechten uit de moderne Mexicaanse keuken, zoals we die zelf het liefste koken en eten.

At Rosario we work with a small, frequently changing, menu, with dishes from modern Mexican cuisine, the way we love to eat and cook it.

Delicious modern Mexican food to enjoy by yourself or with friends/loved ones, nice drinks, good vibes, friendly and amazing personnel! I do recommend to make a reservation online just in case, just to make sure that you have a table reserved.

To start of I had the TACOS DE CAMARONES (2) with shrimp, chipotle crema topped with red cabbage and samphire. It was an flavour bomb!
So good! The balance of flavours was spot on!

After that I had the SERE DE PESCADO
Pan, a fried corvina in a red coconut sauce.
A Caribbean Mexican dish from the Garifuna community. It was soooo good!
The fish was perfectly cooked and the sauce just elevated the entire dish! The freshly baked bread that they also serve with the dish is great to scoop up all that tasty goodness off the plate.

For my 3rd meal I had the TACOS DE SUADERO (4), a Mexico City classic. Crispy fried beef brisket with a tomatillo salsa. It was tasty, and good hit of salt... although a bit oily (but that's just my personal opinion). The lime definitely helped to add some acidity to counter the saltiness and oily flavour.

To finish it off I had the caramel flan for dessert with a cappuccino + almond syrup on the side.
A nice and sweet way to finish off the food experience!

Would I recommend this place and come back in the future? Absolutely!!!","published_at":"7 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-06-09T09:52:21","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOTMx8zWUcWVauA5BUABrrG2M5h_i_AcCXWi7W3=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPhG2W82t06EUxHww9J_EFCJOVAdx-Dh0-UhRin=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMI77uLb9to1nd1NzPjsStLHGRZK-fPUgE7MWbP=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipON0GZe3AfZheeUTupRcQ_EvTc4mWm22lYCuXv1=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNYX1llaTdnRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Dimitri Kr","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113486259251423457521?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Phenomenal food in a cozy small place within Jordan's beautiful narrow streets. name: Madre
description: Ontdek Madre, het leukste Mexicaanse restaurant in Amsterdam! Geniet van modern Mexicaanse gerechten bereid met verse ingredienten, zoveel lokaal en biologische gesourced. Of je nu zin hebt in een gezellige avond in het restaurant of in lekkere drankjes in de cocktailbar,Madre biedt de perfecte sfeer. Goed nieuws: we zijn nu ook op maandag geopend! Madre is de ideale plek voor iedereen die op zoek is naar Mexicaans eten in Amsterdam. Reserveer snel en ervaar het leukste restaurant in de stad!

You walk in through a narrow corridor, past a small bar and into the main area of the restaurant which has a modern 1920s vibe with satin lounges, as well as tables. To the right there is a huge open kitchen  where you can watch the kitchen staff prepare your meal. Service was very good! Attentive, friendly but not annoying. Empty plates were removed almost instantly and we could order quickly aswell. The food was DELICIOUS! All veggie and vegan and the concept allows to share. We had the mushroom tacos which were super tasty, the cauliflower wings (also great) and (the cherry on top) roasted Yacon with mole sauce. The Yacon really surprised me! The mix of the rather crisp and sweet tasting root mixed with the roasted aroma and the mole was perfect! Never had this before and I was definitely impressed!!
They also have their own Madre blond (in collaboration with Homeland Brewery) which tastes exotic and fresh and complements the dishes very well.
We spent 60EU in total and were saturated and satisfied. Definitely worth a visit!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-28T13:40:01","response_from_owner_text":"Hello Alina!

It would have been great if they had included the tortilla chips and freshly-made guacamole in the set, especially since they prepare it right at your table, which looked pretty impressive.

Overall, the price was fair, but I did leave a bit hungry. Still, the quality of the food made it worth trying.

The only downside was being charged 9EU for a Heineken, which was surprising.

name: Cafe Nieuw Amsterdam
description:
Midden in de bruisende Haarlemmerbuurt is Cafe Nieuw Amsterdam; de plek voor moderne bistro klassiekers, lekker lang tafelen, goede wijnen en cocktails. En dat allemaal in hartje Amsterdam, met het West-Indisch Huis als ons prachtig decor.

Een heerlijke plek om te lunchen, brunchen, lachen, borrelen, drinken, dineren en voornamelijk om het leven te vieren. Gezelligheid, ambacht en liefde zijn ons motto, dat proef en voel je. Kom je langs?

We begrijpen dat er enige verwarring kan zijn rondom de houdbaarheidsdatum van de producten die u heeft gekocht. We willen benadrukken dat we ons best doen om deze informatie zo transparant mogelijk te communiceren. Alle producten op onze website worden duidelijk gepresenteerd met hun houdbaarheidsdatum, en we vragen bij elke toevoeging aan uw winkelwagen uw akkoord met deze datum. Daarnaast wordt de houdbaarheidsinformatie nogmaals vermeld in uw winkelwagen, tijdens het afrekenproces en op de factuur die u ontvangt. Desondanks begrijpen we dat het voor sommigen nog steeds niet volledig duidelijk is, en we zullen intern bekijken hoe we dit nog duidelijker kunnen verwoorden.

Ons doel is om ervoor te zorgen dat al onze klanten volledig op de hoogte zijn van de houdbaarheidsstatus van de producten die ze bij ons kopen, terwijl we tegelijkertijd streven naar het tegengaan van voedselverspilling door producten met een beperkte of verlopen houdbaarheidsdatum tegen gereduceerde prijzen aan te bieden. De uiteindelijke beslissing om deze producten al dan niet aan te schaffen ligt altijd bij de klant. 

Ondanks ons eerdere klantcontact om tot een oplossing te komen, hebben wij als gebaar van goodwill de kosten van de producten teruggestort op uw rekening. Het is teleurstellend om te horen dat u nog steeds niet tevreden bent en dat u zich zo voelt. We willen graag dat al onze klanten een positieve ervaring hebben met onze service, en we betreuren het dat we niet aan uw verwachtingen hebben kunnen voldoen.

All products on our website are clearly presented with their best before date, and we request your agreement to this date with each addition to your shopping cart. In addition, the shelf life information is mentioned again in your shopping cart, during the checkout process and on the invoice you receive. Nevertheless, we understand that it is still not completely clear to some, and we will look internally at how we can express this even more clearly.

Our aim is to ensure that all our customers are fully aware of the shelf life status of the products they purchase from us, whilst at the same time aiming to reduce food waste by offering products with a limited or expired shelf life at reduced prices offer. The final decision whether or not to purchase these products always rests with the customer. 

Despite our previous customer contact to find a solution, we have refunded the costs of the products to your account as a gesture of goodwill. It is disappointing to hear that you are still not satisfied and that you feel this way. We want all our customers to have a positive experience with our service, and we regret that we were unable to meet your expectations.

name: SOIL Vegan Cafe - WEST
description: Welcome to SOIL Vegan Cafe - WEST, your go-to vegan restaurant in Amsterdam! We proudly serve a mouthwatering range of vegan comfort food designed to delight your taste buds. Whether you're looking for hearty meals or light bites, our menu has something for everyone. Enhance your dining experience by pairing your meal with our carefully selected artisanal beers and natural wines. Our cafe features a warm and inviting atmosphere that welcomes all. If you're hunting for a vegan-friendly spot in Amsterdam, look no further--SOIL is the perfect place to indulge in vibrant, plant-based cuisine!

name: TAQUERIA LOCAL DEALER FOOD INC.
description:
Searching for an authentic Mexican restaurant Amsterdam? Local Dealer Food Inc. is a real family business serving up the true taste of Mexico!

Enjoy our mouthwatering tacos, zesty ceviches, refreshing margaritas, craft beers, and natural wines, all made with authentic flavors and a modern twist.

Join us every Saturday and Sunday from 12:00 to 16:00 for our lively Mexican brunch.  

Come experience the vibrant atmosphere and heartfelt, home-cooked flavor that only a family-run spot can offer!
Mexican Diner - Ceviches ~ Coctails~ Cervezas ~ Natural Wines

name: Senor Mostachio
description:
Welcome to Senor Mostachio, we pride in serving authentic Mexican cuisine in a relaxed and sophisticated setting in the heart of Amsterdam. Celebrate everything that is wonderful about Mexican cuisine by experiencing Senor Mostachio mexican cantina.

Senor Mostachio offers an impressive array of traditional Mexican dishes sure to please even the most discriminating palate. Indulging on home-made tortilla chips and fresh salsa or traditional tacos. Carefully prepared which compliments any meal. At Senor Mostachio we offer an amazing assortment of imported beers, cocktails, and margaritas! Perfect place for groups!

name: Oaxaca Amsterdam
description: An ancient gastronomic heritage. Eating at OAXACA is like being transported to Mexico. Through ancestral techniques, planting a multitude of Mexican produces in our gardens and "milpas", and cooking with native ingredients. We're talking about nixtamalized corn dough ground on volcanic stone. Knowledge of all the chiles, "soasados" and "tatemados", charcoal-grilled fish, pre-Hispanic "moles" and stews. Guacamole prepared in a "molcajete" and spicy sauces, just as they are made and enjoyed in Mexico.

However, I have been two times in Oaxaca restaurant and it has not disappointed. Mostly if you think the great lengths they went into transforming this corner into a feel like a restaurant in Oaxaca city experience, they even brought the artisan crafts from there. name: Louie Louie
description: Louie Louie is where culinary flair meets nightlife excitement. By day, it's a happening bar offering delicious eats with a twist. But when the sun sets, it morphs into a buzzing hotspot, especially on Friday and Saturday nights when top DJs spin cool tunes on an amazing sound system. With its delicious food & cool vibes, Louie Louie is the go-to spot for those seeking a hip fusion of dining and music.

description:
We're Cabron the Mexican Foodbar!

Located right at the Albert Cuyp Market we're bringing the rich and mouthwatering flavours of Latin America together. Come and join us for authentic food, proper tequila and fine craft beers at the cities most beloved hotspot!

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQa29yWTdRRRAB","rating":4,"name":"Ian D","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109737361272807872264?hl=en-GB","review_text":"We tried the pancakes at this restaurant, as it's highly recommended when visiting Amsterdam. It was quite busy when we arrived, but we managed to get a table for four. The service was friendly, though we had to wait almost an hour for our orders. This was understandable, as a large group was seated upstairs.

I ordered green tea, and when I asked for a refill of hot water, they kindly provided a fresh tea bag along with the hot water, which was charged EU1.50 as listed on the menu.

The interior was charming, with lots of beautiful paintings on the walls. Overall, it's a must-try spot if you're in the area!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-22T20:45:55","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Ian,

Thank you for sharing your detailed review! We're glad you enjoyed our pancakes and the charming ambiance of our restaurant, especially the paintings that make our space unique. It's great to know our team provided friendly service and accommodated your request for a tea refill.

We appreciate your patience during the wait, especially with the large group upstairs, and hope the delicious pancakes made up for the delay. We're honored to be on your must-try list and look forward to welcoming you back on your next visit to Amsterdam!

Warm regards,

Dutch Pancake Masters Team

name: Calle Ocho
description:
The best Miami streetfood restaurant land ate-night cocktailbar in the Pijp area in Amsterdam.

Calle Ocho: a warm, fun and buzzy ambience with some "gekkigheid". A place where you can take your tinder-date, grandmother or your volleyball team.

From Cuban to Mexican and from Caribbean to Tex-Mex. Calle Ocho is all of that in a nutshell. Our chefs translated this to a small menu which changes regularly.

name: Cantina Caliente - Cocina Latina
description:
Our definition of cantina is a place where you can come for a coffee, lunch, dinner some snacks or just a drink.

We are specialized in Latin-American food and serve authentic dishes like hand-made blue corn tacos, Peruvian ceviche, Argentinian beef, empanadas and many vegan options.

We have an extended menu of tequilas, mezcales, pisco, wines, beers and cocktails.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNuLXQyTkxREAE","rating":5,"name":"Idil Gnosti","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114041679726990389274?hl=en-GB","review_text":"OBSESSED with their Quesabirria, it's only the best thing I ate in Amsterdam in relation to birria. I even drank the birria after dipping my quesadillas in it. And try their tacos please because they are insanely good, I ate like 8 of them. And definitely do yourself a favor and order a couple of their drinks. The spicy margarita, Paloma and the Michelada was literally insane. Michelada is this tomatoey beer cocktail and it's like Bloody Mary and Beer had a baby and produced this drink. It's insane! With the weekend specials being priced at 3euros per taco, this is the most affordable taco in Amsterdam, yet some of the best around. name: Salsa Shop
description: Discover the vibrant flavors of Mexico right in the heart of Amsterdam at Salsa Shop NDSM Kade. This quick service Mexicaans restaurant offers a tantalising menu of traditional Mexican dishes, perfect for a delicious lunch or dinner. Whether you're craving spicy nachos, hearty burritos, or fresh guacamole, you'll be spoilt for choice. Conveniently located near you, it's the perfect spot for a quick bite or a leisurely meal. So, if you're searching for 'Mexicaans eten in de buurt' or 'Mexicaans restaurant Amsterdam', look no further than Salsa Shop NDSM Kade. Enjoy the best Mexican food in town in a warm and welcoming setting!

name: Salsa Shop
description: Indulge in the rich, vibrant flavors of Mexico at the Salsa Shop Javastraat - your go-to Mexican quick service restaurant in Amsterdam. Conveniently located near you, this hotspot is the perfect destination for lunch or a delicious dinner. Whether it's a quick bite or a sit-down meal, Salsa Shop Javastraat offers a vast range of delicious Mexican food.

name: Alfonso's Mexican & Grill Restaurant
description:
In the beloved Utrechtsestraat in Amsterdam, located since 1986, you will find Alfonso's, an authentic Mexican restaurant. In a lively and friendly atmosphere you can enjoy the many famous specialties Mexico offers.
Several delicious fajitas, tacos burritos and tortillas adorn the menu.
Of course you can drink one of the cool Mexican beers or margaritas with the specialties on the table. You conclude your dinner with a tasty dessert or, for the real lover, a hearty coffee with a glass of tequila.

- Enchilada: 5+/5 
- Burrito: 5/5 
- Taco: 4/5 
- Nachos Sonora: 4/5 
Price: 4/5 
Service: 4/5 

On my second visit to this establishment, I found that the ambiance and service continued to be fairly standard - nothing particularly noteworthy, but comfortable enough for a casual dining experience.

The highlight here is unquestionably the food, which stands a notch above the ordinary. We started with the Nachos Sonora, which, while bursting with flavor, fell short in portion size, especially as a dish advertised for two. The toppings, too, were on the scantier side, which was a bit of a letdown.

Moving on to the main course, the Combinacion Alfonso's was a mixed bag. The taco was average, failing to make much of an impression. However, the enchilada and burrito were a different story altogether - absolutely divine. These dishes alone make the restaurant worth visiting, elevating the overall culinary experience.

So, while it doesn't quite hit the five-star mark for me, it's definitely a solid choice for good food. name: Salsa Shop
description: Looking for a Mexican restaurant in Amsterdam? Salsa Shop Amsterdam at Rembrandt Square is your top choice. Enjoy the authentic Mexican food experience right here in the heart of Amsterdam. With a variety of delicious options available, whether you are craving for lunch, lekker eten, or simply want to explore restaurants near you, Salsa Shop has got you covered. It stands out among Amsterdam restaurants, offering a unique blend of traditional and modern Mexicaans food that you won't find elsewhere. Experience the best Mexicaans restaurant Amsterdam has to offer at Salsa Shop.

name: Los Pilones
description:
FROM MEXICO TO AMSTERDAM
From Mexico to Amsterdam
How it all came to be...

It all started in 2001 when Los Pilones opened the doors at Kerkstraat 63 and introduced authentic Mexican cuisine in The Netherlands!

Los Pilones is a Mexican cantina style concept, serving fresh home made food and drinks in a colourful and vibrant atmosphere - a fiesta straight from Mexico to Amsterdam. You can drop in for tacos, enchiladas, flautas, quesadillas, fresh margaritas, micheladas, over 200 different kinds of 100% agave tequilas and mezcal.

Pilon in Mexico means "a little extra" and that is exactly what we intend to give you when you visit Los Pilones!

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzcDR2Y3ZRRRAB","rating":3,"name":"Marius Alzbergas","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108484636811084637828?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I love ramen, and past weeks I've tried quite few ramen restaurants, every restaurant offers same dish, yet it's taste each and every time is whole new experience. Today i've visited this restaurant only because it has high amount of good reviews,  but my experience was not so great.
I really like the atmosphere, it's quiet and calm.
Service was ok, but i didn't like the fact that i was moved from the seats because it was closed and after a minute one of their collegues took same place we had at first.
Now about why i've visited that restaurant in first place - ramen. In my opinion there are 3 main ingredients: broth, meat, and pasta, and  I had kinda weird experience, pasta was really hot to eat, broth was warm and toppings cold, that makes me think that it was microwaved, also after we ordered plate was ready in max 3 minutes.
Broth taste ok, but i felt it was a bit too thick compared to the taste.
Pasta was difficult to eat because it was twisted, after a few minutes it became soft, and to the taste it felt like it was not homemade pasta but the pre made from the store.
And as i've mentioned earlier, meat and other toppins was cold.
I could not give more than 2 stars.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-19T16:33:27","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPaMyOcr-6NmIntIVIoWhXRlXzwtO_wf9hYSv7H=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUMzeS1LSzB3RRAB","rating":5,"name":"Arina S","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108072746501179241882?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Very nice place. Like many other reviewers on Yelp, we had a hotel credit to use and we eagerly planned to use it at this restaurant.

We made a reservation at 8 and it was not full in the restaurant yet we barely had any staff wait on us. We ordered the calamari (not pictured), short rib, broccolini and cauliflower. While we saw the manager come out multiple time to check in other tables, multiple times our food came out from the kitchen and I watched it sit there and not be brought to us. Consequently, when our short rib was finally brought to us it had been sitting for five minutes and was inedible. We do not waste food and my husband I left more than half of the short rib on the plate. When our waitress cleared our table it was quite awkward because she did not even comment or ask how our meal was.

After we paid and left, we spoke to the Kimpton DeWitt team and asked to give feedback on our experience. All credit to the wonderful staff at the Kimpton who heard us, speedily got the manager (who was the same waitstaff who did not check in with us) and rectified the experience. When we spoke to Jasper, the manager at Celia's that evening, he heard us and said repeatedly it was not their intention while not offering any rectification for our subpar experience.

I want to contrast that experience with our breakfast experience the next day at Celia. We had Evalina (name, spelling?) who was so thoughtful and engaged with all customers who came in. So much so that even when I sneezed she was right there saying bless you. She treated every customer with courtesy and respect. When we asked her her name she shook our hand and asked us if we wanted any drinks to go too. Service like that (mind you on a busy morning with the buffet) was such a stark contrast from our slow Sunday dinner experience. I want to make sure other diners are aware of the inconsistencies and the areas where the restaurant could improve.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-08T23:13:30","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOd5m7oawDzKqQTbCB5oTRZB9PLUb1d-vTkfOyO=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURQblllS1RREAE","rating":4,"name":"Dan Thompson","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109826952670419327272?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Food was incredible, the best burger I've had in years. name: Brasserie Lolita
description: Are you looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than Brasserie Lolita in de Pijp! This gezellig French restaurant is the perfect restaurant in Amsterdam. With delicious French dishes and a cozy atmosphere, it's the perfect spot to enjoy a meal with friends or family. Plus, it's located in the heart of Amsterdam Zuid, de Pijp, making it a great hotspot for all your dining needs. Join for the best dinner or come for some of the best cocktails and have fun at the bar. Brasserie Lolita is well known in Amsterdam and the hotspot for the locals in de Pijp. If you are looking for a French restaurant right in the heart of de Pijp Amsterdam, come check out Brasserie Lolita today! Open till 3am on weekend days.

name: Restaurant Argentalia Amsterdam
description:
Argentalia is a fusion restaurant, a unique culinary blend of the flavorful traditions of Italy and Argentina. Located in the city's heart, we take our patrons on a gastronomic journey, merging the rustic charm of Argentine food with the subtlety of Italian gastronomy.

Our menu is centered around fresh ingredients and authentic recipes. It embodies the hearty Argentine flavors famous for its robust meats, with Italy's rich heritage of fresh pasta, aromatic sauces, and divine cheese and wine.
Argentalia's aesthetic reflects its menu - a beautiful amalgamation of rustic Argentine warmth and timeless Italian elegance.

name: Maydanoz
description:
Ontdek de geheimen van de Turkse keuken.Smaken waar je blij van wordt.
Maydanoz is een mediterraan restaurant in Amsterdam waar de Turkse keuken centraal staat, met een menu dat zowel vleesliefhebbers als vegetariers en veganisten aanspreekt.
De gerechten worden bereid met de beste ingredienten en weerspiegelen de rijke diversiteit van de mediterrane keuken.
Van traditionele kebab tot verfijnde vegetarische schotels, bij Maydanoz is er voor elke smaakpapil wel iets te vinden. Uw nieuwe favoriete plek voor tapas in Amsterdam! Onze uitgebreide tapaskaart biedt een heerlijke mix van koude en warme hapjes, geinspireerd op de Turkse en Mediterrane keuken. Deel kleine gerechtjes met vrienden of familie en ontdek de veelzijdigheid van onze smaken.

name: De Burgerfabriek
description:
You can find us in one of the most international known neighbourhoods of Amsterdam, "The red light district", an area full of history and controversy, which has been changing rapidly the last years, evolving into an eclectic mixture of local flavours and foreign cultures, where past and tradition meet future and avant-garde.

The concept of Burgerfabriek is a combination of old essence in a contemporary suit.

We come back to basics: fresh, fast, flavourful food pimped with a modern twist. An industrial and rough, but cushy space; and a kitchen based on organic, primary, quality ingredients, with a touch of sophistication

Burgerfabriek features also comfortable tables where you can tap your own beer.
Come Enjoy the Burgerfabriek experience

name: Cafe del Mondo
description:
Cafe del Mondo is gelegen aan de Amsterdamse Nieuwmarkt, midden in Mokum.
Kom binnen voor een heerlijk ontbijt, lunch, borrel of diner.
Sinds 1994 is het een begrip in Amsterdam en de plek om alle Ajax wedstrijden te bekijken.

name: Burgerfabriek Express-Nieuwendijk 142 Amsterdam
description:
You can find us in one of the most international known neighbourhoods of Amsterdam, "The red light district", Nieuwendijk shopping area, an area full of history and controversy, which has been changing rapidly the last years, evolving into an eclectic mixture of local flavours and foreign cultures, where past and tradition meet future and avant-garde.

The concept of Burgerfabriek is a combination of old essence in a contemporary suit.

We come back to basics: fresh, fast, flavourful food pimped with a modern twist. An industrial and rough, but cushy space; and a kitchen based on organic, primary, quality ingredients, with a touch of sophistication

name: Fiona
description:
Fiona, your go-to spot for Mexican cuisine in the heart of Warmoesstraat. Our menu is bursting with flavor, featuring all of your favorite dishes like tacos, nachos and quesadillas, as well as some of our own unique creations.

But it's not just the food that sets us apart - our atmosphere is just as vibrant and lively as the streets of Mexico. Our cozy and colorful interior, complete with traditional Mexican decor, will transport you south of the border.

So come on in, grab a seat, and let us take you on a culinary journey through Mexico. Whether you're in the mood for a quick bite or a full-on fiesta, Fiona has something for everyone. !Buen provecho!

The menu is thoughtfully curated, offering a mix of classic and innovative dishes that highlight fresh, seasonal ingredients. Every bite feels like it's crafted with care and passion.

The ambiance is inviting, with a laid-back yet refined vibe that's perfect for anything from a casual lunch to a special dinner. The staff are attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable, always ready with great recommendations. Fiona's is the kind of place where you feel right at home and leave with plans to return. Discover why we're the go-to Mexican eatery in Amsterdam!

name: Bar Lempicka
description: Bar Lempicka is een stijlvolle bar - brasserie in het hart van Amsterdam, met een zonovergoten terras aan de Amstel. Drink een cocktail of een van de vele speciaal bieren aan de indrukwekkende bar binnen of neem front-row buiten plaats om lekker mensen en bootjes te kijken. Bij Bar Lempicka kun je elke dag van vroeg tot laat het leven vieren met mediterrane shared dining gerechtjes. Door de unieke locatie op de hoek Sarphatistraat/Amstel, op een steenworp afstand van theater Carre en de Hermitage, is Bar Lempicka de ideale uitvalsbasis voor theater- of museumbezoek.

name: Ritos Amsterdam - Fusion Mex & Bowls
description:
The first Mexican and Pokebowl restaurant. Get your legendary Mexican burritos, fresh Pokebowls and sushi burritos right here in Amsterdam, The Hague, Amersfoort, Eindhoven or Utrecht.

Come in and visit us!
Eindhoven: Nieuwstraat 25
Amersfoort: Kamp 16
Utrecht: Potterstraat 8
Den Haag: Korte Poten 16
Amsterdam: Van Woustraat 45H

name: Coco's Outback
description:
Looking for the ultimate spot in Amsterdam that combines a sports bar, restaurant, and nightclub experience?
Coco's Outback the no.1 sportsbar in Amsterdam has it all! Located in the heart of the city, this lively Australian-themed venue offers a vibrant atmosphere perfect for sports fans, food lovers, and night owls. Enjoy live sports on big screens, savor hearty dishes like burgers, wings, BBQ, and dance the night away with great music and cocktails. Whether you're after a casual lunch, thrilling game-day vibes, or a wild night out, Coco's Outback is your go-to destination in Amsterdam

Our server Arash was super friendly and helped us with the menu, as we couldn't decide what to have, we left with very full bellies and most importantly it didn't break the bank.

Hopefully we will return on our next visit to Amsterdam :-)

featured_reviews:
[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmOUotN2xBRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Svenja H","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116004883539518143153?hl=en-GB","review_text":"THE MEXICAN is a very small hidden restaurant not far from the Dam, therefore extremely central. We came here for an early dinner on Boxing Day with two adults and a child.

We ordered Jalapeno Poppers, Fajitas, Chicken Wings and drinks. Everything was served within an acceptable time frame and even though we only ordered one main dish, nobody looked at us in a funny way or made us feel less welcome.

The food was great. It's of course not the top tier authentic Mexican cuisine you'll find here, but we found everything to be delicious and tasty measured by European Mexican restaurant standards. Saying this is more of an Indian restaurant cause the food is spicy is nothing but ridiculous. Educate yourself before making a fool of yourself on the internet.

The prices at this restaurant are nearly unbeatable. Main courses come at around EU18 per dish, starters are EU8-10. You can eat much worse for much more money when you're in Amsterdam, especially around the Dam.

The service could be a lot more friendly aha welcoming, that much I'll give you critical people. But we were still treated with respect and never felt unwelcome or overlooked.

We'd come here again any given time. name: Agabi Santa Maria
description: Mexicaans en Argentijns restaurant Agabi Santa Maria is sinds 2004 gelegen aan het Waterlooplein, in het levendige centrum van Amsterdam en wordt omringd door de beste en leukste theaters, musea en historische bezienswaardigheden van Amsterdam. We bevinden ons op slechts een steenworp afstand van culturele pareltjes zoals de Nationale Opera & Ballet, Hermitage, Carre en nog veel meer. We heten u van harte welkom om bij ons te genieten van een heerlijke maaltijd voor of na uw theater- of museumbezoek!

I recently visited Sushito via ClassPass on May 28th, but accidentally placed my order at the wrong location. When I arrived, I politely asked the waitress behind the bar if she could call the other location to see if anything could be done. She was incredibly polite and promptly checked with the chef manager in the kitchen.

To my utter shock, the Italian chef came out and began yelling at me, insisting that nothing could be done about my mistake. He continued to scream, even as I stood there in disbelief at his reaction. I calmly asked him to stop, but he persisted. The staff, who appeared just as shocked as I was, looked on helplessly.

I informed the chef that his behavior had cost them a loyal customer who had previously enjoyed many visits to Sushito. I have worked in the hospitality industry for ten years and have never encountered such unprofessional and aggressive conduct from a staff member.

This experience has completely soured my view of Sushito, and I will not be returning.  The extreme rudeness and lack of basic customer service were appalling. If you value respectful and polite service, I would recommend looking elsewhere.

name: Salsa Shop
description: Discover the authentic flavors of Mexico at Salsa Shop Amsterdam Zuidas, a hidden gem for Mexican food lovers. This Mexicaans restaurant serves up mouthwatering meals that will take your taste buds on a flavourful journey. Whether you're searching for the perfect lunch spot, a restaurant near you, or craving delicious Mexican cuisine, Salsa Shop Amsterdam Zuidas is the place to be. Enjoy scrumptious dishes like spicy tacos, flavorful burritos, and more, all freshly prepared with high-quality ingredients. So, if you're in Amsterdam and looking for a restaurant near you, don't miss out on this top-rated Mexicaans restaurant. Experience the best of Mexican cuisine at Salsa Shop Amsterdam Zuidas.

name: Mexicaans Cafe-Restaurant La Margarita Amsterdam
description: La Margarita. Het Mexicaans restaurant van Amsterdam! Al meer dan dertig jaar een begrip. Gevestigd in de Langebrugsteeg nr 6, het bruisend hart van Amsterdam. Tussen het Rokin en de Nes; op loopafstand van het Rembrandtplein en Dam, ontvangen wij u in een levendige en vriendelijke ambiance. Ons restaurant is geschikt voor een diner voor twee, maar ook voor bruiloften, recepties en groepen. Tot maximaal 98 personen kunt a la carte bestellen of, indien u dit wenst, kiezen voor een samengesteld menu.tevens zijn wij gespecialiseerd in glutenvrij eten

My partner and I recently visited this Argentinian restaurant, and while the prices were reasonable, the overall experience was far from enjoyable due to the staff's behavior.

From the moment we arrived, we felt uncomfortable. The staff repeatedly stared at us, to the point where it felt like they were sizing us up. Before our food arrived, one staff member stood right behind my chair with his hand on it, listening in on our private conversation, which was incredibly intrusive. To make matters worse, while we were eating, I was bizarrely told to switch to another seat for no apparent reason, further disrupting the experience.

When it came to the food, the ribs were overly sweet and sickly, and the salad looked nothing like the menu photos. While it did fill me up for the evening, the quality left much to be desired.

The final interaction was the most off-putting. When the bill arrived, the older waiter made a point of highlighting the tip section and seemed displeased when I chose not to add one. He sulked, walked away without thanking us, and didn't even say goodbye.

This restaurant has potential with its fair pricing and ambiance, but the staff's attitude and the food quality need serious improvement to make it a place worth recommending.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-19T15:32:36","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR6NWR2SHN3RRAB","rating":2,"name":"Abu Isaac","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115443352950219315272?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Food was lovely. name: Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Noord
description: Maak de Mexicaan in je los en bestel de lekkerste Mexicaanse gerechten eenvoudig bij Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Noord. Je kunt kiezen uit onder andere onze befaamde Tacos, Rijkgevulde Burritos, heerlijke Quesadillas en natuurlijk onze beroemde Nachos. Als afsluiter kun je kiezen uit onze verrassende Taco Mundo Ice Creams of bijvoorbeeld onze onweerstaanbare Churros. Wat je ook kiest... Je tovert met een druk op de knop jouw avond om in een Mexican FIESTA!

name: taqueria lima west
description:
Crazy good Mexican food. A whole lot of tacos, burritos, bowls and snacks, Taqueria LIMA has got it all!
Our chefs serve you the best classics like the taco Al Pastor, homemade braised beef or pulled chicken. But also a great Vegan Jack Fruit taco.
Come taste our light, fresh and easy going Mexican street food. El Super Taco Loco!

name: Taco Mundo Amsterdam Oud-Zuid
description: Maak de Mexicaan in je los en bestel de lekkerste Mexicaanse gerechten eenvoudig bij Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Oud Zuid. Je kunt kiezen uit onder andere onze befaamde Tacos, Rijkgevulde Burritos, heerlijke Quesadillas en natuurlijk onze beroemde Nachos. Als afsluiter kun je kiezen uit onze verrassende Taco Mundo Ice Creams of bijvoorbeeld onze onweerstaanbare Churros. Wat je ook kiest... Je tovert met een druk op de knop jouw avond om in een Mexican FIESTA!

name: Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Oud West
description: Maak de Mexicaan in je los en bestel de lekkerste Mexicaanse gerechten eenvoudig bij Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Oud West. Je kunt kiezen uit onder andere onze befaamde Tacos, Rijkgevulde Burritos, heerlijke Quesadillas en natuurlijk onze beroemde Nachos. Als afsluiter kun je kiezen uit onze verrassende Taco Mundo Ice Creams of bijvoorbeeld onze onweerstaanbare Churros. Wat je ook kiest... Je tovert met een druk op de knop jouw avond om in een Mexican FIESTA!
